16/*! \file
17 * \brief
18 * Portable SPNEGO implementation.
19 *
20 * This is part of a portable implementation of the SPNEGO protocol
21 * (RFCs 2478 and 4178). This implementation uses the RFC 4178 ASN.1
22 * module but is not a full implementation of the RFC 4178 protocol;
23 * at the moment, we only support GSS-TSIG with Kerberos
24 * authentication, so we only need enough of the SPNEGO protocol to
25 * support that.
26 *
27 * The files that make up this portable SPNEGO implementation are:
28 * \li spnego.c (this file)
29 * \li spnego.h (API SPNEGO exports to the rest of lib/dns)
30 * \li spnego.asn1 (SPNEGO ASN.1 module)
31 * \li spnego_asn1.c (routines generated from spngo.asn1)
32 * \li spnego_asn1.pl (perl script to generate spnego_asn1.c)
33 *
34 * Everything but the functions exported in spnego.h is static, to
35 * avoid possible conflicts with other libraries (particularly Heimdal,
36 * since much of this code comes from Heimdal by way of mod_auth_kerb).
37 *
38 * spnego_asn1.c is shipped as part of lib/dns because generating it
39 * requires both Perl and the Heimdal ASN.1 compiler. See
40 * spnego_asn1.pl for further details. We've tried to eliminate all
41 * compiler warnings from the generated code, but you may see a few
42 * when using a compiler version we haven't tested yet.
43 */
44

320/*
321 * Force the oid arrays to be uint64_t aligned to silence warnings
322 * about the arrays not being properly aligned for (void *).
323 */
324typedef union { unsigned char b[8]; uint64_t _align; } aligned8;
325typedef union { unsigned char b[16]; uint64_t _align[2]; } aligned16;
326
327static aligned16 gss_krb5_mech_oid_bytes = {
328 { 0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x12, 0x01, 0x02, 0x02 }
329};
330
331static gss_OID_desc gss_krb5_mech_oid_desc = {
332 9, gss_krb5_mech_oid_bytes.b
333};
334
335static gss_OID GSS_KRB5_MECH = &gss_krb5_mech_oid_desc;
336
337static aligned16 gss_mskrb5_mech_oid_bytes = {

339};
340
341static gss_OID_desc gss_mskrb5_mech_oid_desc = {
342 9, gss_mskrb5_mech_oid_bytes.b
343};
344

373/* mod_auth_kerb.c */
374
375static bool
376cmp_gss_type(gss_buffer_t token, gss_OID gssoid)
377{
378 unsigned char *p;
379 size_t len;
380
381 if (token->length == 0U)
382 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
383
384 p = token->value;
385 if (*p++ != 0x60)
386 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
387 len = *p++;
388 if (len & 0x80) {
389 if ((len & 0x7f) > 4U)
390 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
391 p += len & 0x7f;
392 }
393 if (*p++ != 0x06)
394 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
395
396 if (((OM_uint32) *p++) != gssoid->length)
397 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
398
399 return (!isc_safe_memequal(p, gssoid->elements, gssoid->length));
400}

402/* accept_sec_context.c */
403/*
404 * SPNEGO wrapper for Kerberos5 GSS-API kouril@ics.muni.cz, 2003 (mostly
405 * based on Heimdal code)
406 */
407
408static OM_uint32
409code_NegTokenArg(OM_uint32 * minor_status,
410 const NegTokenResp * resp,
411 unsigned char **outbuf,
412 size_t * outbuf_size)
413{
414 OM_uint32 ret;
415 u_char *buf;
416 size_t buf_size, buf_len = 0;
417
418 buf_size = 1024;
419 buf = malloc(buf_size);
420 if (buf == NULL) {
421 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
422 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
423 }
424 do {
425 ret = encode_NegTokenResp(buf + buf_size - 1,
426 buf_size,
427 resp, &buf_len);
428 if (ret == 0) {
429 size_t tmp;
430
431 ret = der_put_length_and_tag(buf + buf_size - buf_len - 1,
432 buf_size - buf_len,
433 buf_len,
434 ASN1_C_CONTEXT,
435 CONS,
436 1,
437 &tmp);
438 if (ret == 0)
439 buf_len += tmp;
440 }
441 if (ret) {
442 if (ret == ASN1_OVERFLOW) {
443 u_char *tmp;
444
445 buf_size *= 2;
446 tmp = realloc(buf, buf_size);
447 if (tmp == NULL) {
448 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
449 free(buf);
450 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
451 }
452 buf = tmp;
453 } else {
454 *minor_status = ret;
455 free(buf);
456 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
457 }
458 }
459 } while (ret == ASN1_OVERFLOW);
460
461 *outbuf = malloc(buf_len);
462 if (*outbuf == NULL) {
463 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
464 free(buf);
465 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
466 }
467 memmove(*outbuf, buf + buf_size - buf_len, buf_len);
468 *outbuf_size = buf_len;
469
470 free(buf);
471
472 return (GSS_S_COMPLETE);
473}
474
475static OM_uint32
476send_reject(OM_uint32 * minor_status,
477 gss_buffer_t output_token)
478{
479 NegTokenResp resp;
480 OM_uint32 ret;
481
482 resp.negState = malloc(sizeof(*resp.negState));
483 if (resp.negState == NULL) {
484 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
485 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
486 }
487 *(resp.negState) = reject;
488
489 resp.supportedMech = NULL;
490 resp.responseToken = NULL;
491 resp.mechListMIC = NULL;
492
493 ret = code_NegTokenArg(minor_status, &resp,
494 (unsigned char **)&output_token->value,
495 &output_token->length);
496 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
497 if (ret)
498 return (ret);
499
500 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
501}
502
503static OM_uint32
504send_accept(OM_uint32 * minor_status,
505 gss_buffer_t output_token,
506 gss_buffer_t mech_token,
507 const gss_OID pref)
508{
509 NegTokenResp resp;
510 OM_uint32 ret;
511
512 memset(&resp, 0, sizeof(resp));
513 resp.negState = malloc(sizeof(*resp.negState));
514 if (resp.negState == NULL) {
515 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
516 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
517 }
518 *(resp.negState) = accept_completed;
519
520 resp.supportedMech = malloc(sizeof(*resp.supportedMech));
521 if (resp.supportedMech == NULL) {
522 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
523 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
524 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
525 }
526 ret = der_get_oid(pref->elements,
527 pref->length,
528 resp.supportedMech,
529 NULL);
530 if (ret) {
531 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
532 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
533 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
534 }
535 if (mech_token != NULL && mech_token->length != 0U) {
536 resp.responseToken = malloc(sizeof(*resp.responseToken));
537 if (resp.responseToken == NULL) {
538 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
539 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
540 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
541 }
542 resp.responseToken->length = mech_token->length;
543 resp.responseToken->data = mech_token->value;
544 }
545
546 ret = code_NegTokenArg(minor_status, &resp,
547 (unsigned char **)&output_token->value,
548 &output_token->length);
549 if (resp.responseToken != NULL) {
550 free(resp.responseToken);
551 resp.responseToken = NULL;
552 }
553 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
554 if (ret)
555 return (ret);
556
557 return (GSS_S_COMPLETE);
558}

560OM_uint32
561gss_accept_sec_context_spnego(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
562 gss_ctx_id_t *context_handle,
563 const gss_cred_id_t acceptor_cred_handle,
564 const gss_buffer_t input_token_buffer,
565 const gss_channel_bindings_t input_chan_bindings,
566 gss_name_t *src_name,
567 gss_OID *mech_type,
568 gss_buffer_t output_token,
569 OM_uint32 *ret_flags,
570 OM_uint32 *time_rec,
571 gss_cred_id_t *delegated_cred_handle)
572{
573 NegTokenInit init_token;
574 OM_uint32 major_status = GSS_S_COMPLETE;
575 OM_uint32 minor_status2;
576 gss_buffer_desc ibuf, obuf;
577 gss_buffer_t ot = NULL;
578 gss_OID pref = GSS_KRB5_MECH;
579 unsigned char *buf;
580 size_t buf_size;
581 size_t len, taglen, ni_len;
582 int found = 0;
583 int ret;
584 unsigned i;
585
586 /*
587 * Before doing anything else, see whether this is a SPNEGO
588 * PDU. If not, dispatch to the GSSAPI library and get out.
589 */
590
591 if (cmp_gss_type(input_token_buffer, GSS_SPNEGO_MECH))
592 return (gss_accept_sec_context(minor_status,
593 context_handle,
594 acceptor_cred_handle,
595 input_token_buffer,
596 input_chan_bindings,
597 src_name,
598 mech_type,
599 output_token,
600 ret_flags,
601 time_rec,
602 delegated_cred_handle));
603
604 /*
605 * If we get here, it's SPNEGO.
606 */
607
608 memset(&init_token, 0, sizeof(init_token));
609
610 ret = gssapi_spnego_decapsulate(minor_status, input_token_buffer,
611 &buf, &buf_size, GSS_SPNEGO_MECH);
612 if (ret)
613 return (ret);
614
615 ret = der_match_tag_and_length(buf, buf_size, ASN1_C_CONTEXT, CONS,
616 0, &len, &taglen);
617 if (ret)
618 return (ret);
619
620 ret = decode_NegTokenInit(buf + taglen, len, &init_token, &ni_len);
621 if (ret) {
622 *minor_status = EINVAL; /* XXX */
623 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
624 }
625
626 for (i = 0; !found && i < init_token.mechTypes.len; ++i) {
627 unsigned char mechbuf[17];
628 size_t mech_len;
629
630 ret = der_put_oid(mechbuf + sizeof(mechbuf) - 1,
631 sizeof(mechbuf),
632 &init_token.mechTypes.val[i],
633 &mech_len);
634 if (ret) {
635 free_NegTokenInit(&init_token);
636 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
637 }
638 if (mech_len == GSS_KRB5_MECH->length &&
639 isc_safe_memequal(GSS_KRB5_MECH->elements,
640 mechbuf + sizeof(mechbuf) - mech_len,
641 mech_len))
642 {
643 found = 1;
644 break;
645 }
646 if (mech_len == GSS_MSKRB5_MECH->length &&
647 isc_safe_memequal(GSS_MSKRB5_MECH->elements,
648 mechbuf + sizeof(mechbuf) - mech_len,
649 mech_len))
650 {
651 found = 1;
652 if (i == 0)
653 pref = GSS_MSKRB5_MECH;
654 break;
655 }
656 }
657
658 if (!found) {
659 free_NegTokenInit(&init_token);
660 return (send_reject(minor_status, output_token));
661 }
662
663 if (i == 0 && init_token.mechToken != NULL) {
664 ibuf.length = init_token.mechToken->length;
665 ibuf.value = init_token.mechToken->data;
666
667 major_status = gss_accept_sec_context(minor_status,
668 context_handle,
669 acceptor_cred_handle,
670 &ibuf,
671 input_chan_bindings,
672 src_name,
673 mech_type,
674 &obuf,
675 ret_flags,
676 time_rec,
677 delegated_cred_handle);
678 if (GSS_ERROR(major_status)) {
679 free_NegTokenInit(&init_token);
680 send_reject(&minor_status2, output_token);
681 return (major_status);
682 }
683 ot = &obuf;
684 }
685 ret = send_accept(&minor_status2, output_token, ot, pref);
686 free_NegTokenInit(&init_token);
687 if (ot != NULL && ot->length != 0U)
688 gss_release_buffer(&minor_status2, ot);
689
690 return (ret != GSS_S_COMPLETE ? (OM_uint32) ret : major_status);
691}

693/* decapsulate.c */
694
695static OM_uint32
696gssapi_verify_mech_header(u_char ** str,
697 size_t total_len,
698 const gss_OID mech)
699{
700 size_t len, len_len, mech_len, foo;
701 int e;
702 u_char *p = *str;
703
704 if (total_len < 1U)
705 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
706 if (*p++ != 0x60)
707 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
708 e = der_get_length(p, total_len - 1, &len, &len_len);
709 if (e || 1 + len_len + len != total_len)
710 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
711 p += len_len;
712 if (*p++ != 0x06)
713 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
714 e = der_get_length(p, total_len - 1 - len_len - 1,
715 &mech_len, &foo);
716 if (e)
717 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
718 p += foo;
719 if (mech_len != mech->length)
720 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
721 if (!isc_safe_memequal(p, mech->elements, mech->length))
722 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
723 p += mech_len;
724 *str = p;
725 return (GSS_S_COMPLETE);
726}
727
728/*
729 * Remove the GSS-API wrapping from `in_token' giving `buf and buf_size' Does
730 * not copy data, so just free `in_token'.
731 */
732
733static OM_uint32
734gssapi_spnego_decapsulate(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
735 gss_buffer_t input_token_buffer,
736 unsigned char **buf,
737 size_t *buf_len,
738 const gss_OID mech)
739{
740 u_char *p;
741 OM_uint32 ret;
742
743 p = input_token_buffer->value;
744 ret = gssapi_verify_mech_header(&p,
745 input_token_buffer->length,
746 mech);
747 if (ret) {
748 *minor_status = ret;
749 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
750 }
751 *buf_len = input_token_buffer->length -
752 (p - (u_char *) input_token_buffer->value);
753 *buf = p;
754 return (GSS_S_COMPLETE);
755}

773/* der_get.c */
774
775/*
776 * All decoding functions take a pointer `p' to first position in which to
777 * read, from the left, `len' which means the maximum number of characters we
778 * are able to read, `ret' were the value will be returned and `size' where
779 * the number of used bytes is stored. Either 0 or an error code is returned.
780 */
781
782static int
783der_get_unsigned(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
784 unsigned *ret, size_t *size)
785{
786 unsigned val = 0;
787 size_t oldlen = len;
788
789 while (len--)
790 val = val * 256 + *p++;
791 *ret = val;
792 if (size)
793 *size = oldlen;
794 return (0);
795}
796
797static int
798der_get_int(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
799 int *ret, size_t *size)
800{
801 int val = 0;
802 size_t oldlen = len;
803
804 if (len > 0U) {
805 val = (signed char)*p++;
806 while (--len)
807 val = val * 256 + *p++;
808 }
809 *ret = val;
810 if (size)
811 *size = oldlen;
812 return (0);
813}
814
815static int
816der_get_length(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
817 size_t *val, size_t *size)
818{
819 size_t v;
820
821 if (len <= 0U)
822 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
823 --len;
824 v = *p++;
825 if (v < 128U) {
826 *val = v;
827 if (size)
828 *size = 1;
829 } else {
830 int e;
831 size_t l;
832 unsigned tmp;
833
834 if (v == 0x80U) {
835 *val = ASN1_INDEFINITE;
836 if (size)
837 *size = 1;
838 return (0);
839 }
840 v &= 0x7F;
841 if (len < v)
842 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
843 e = der_get_unsigned(p, v, &tmp, &l);
844 if (e)
845 return (e);
846 *val = tmp;
847 if (size)
848 *size = l + 1;
849 }
850 return (0);
851}
852
853static int
854der_get_octet_string(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
855 octet_string *data, size_t *size)
856{
857 data->length = len;
858 if (len != 0U) {
859 data->data = malloc(len);
860 if (data->data == NULL)
861 return (ENOMEM);
862 memmove(data->data, p, len);
863 } else
864 data->data = NULL;
865 if (size)
866 *size = len;
867 return (0);
868}
869
870static int
871der_get_oid(const unsigned char *p, size_t len, oid *data, size_t *size) {
872 int n;
873 size_t oldlen = len;
874
875 data->components = NULL;
876 data->length = 0;
877 if (len < 1U) {
878 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
879 }
880
881 data->components = malloc(len * sizeof(*data->components));
882 if (data->components == NULL) {
883 return (ENOMEM);
884 }
885 data->components[0] = (*p) / 40;
886 data->components[1] = (*p) % 40;
887 --len;
888 ++p;
889 for (n = 2; len > 0U; ++n) {
890 unsigned u = 0;
891
892 do {
893 --len;
894 u = u * 128 + (*p++ % 128);
895 } while (len > 0U && p[-1] & 0x80);
896 data->components[n] = u;
897 }
898 if (p[-1] & 0x80) {
899 free_oid(data);
900 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
901 }
902 data->length = n;
903 if (size) {
904 *size = oldlen;
905 }
906 return (0);
907}
908
909static int
910der_get_tag(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
911 Der_class *xclass, Der_type *type,
912 int *tag, size_t *size)
913{
914 if (len < 1U)
915 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
916 *xclass = (Der_class) (((*p) >> 6) & 0x03);
917 *type = (Der_type) (((*p) >> 5) & 0x01);
918 *tag = (*p) & 0x1F;
919 if (size)
920 *size = 1;
921 return (0);
922}
923
924static int
925der_match_tag(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
926 Der_class xclass, Der_type type,
927 int tag, size_t *size)
928{
929 size_t l;
930 Der_class thisclass;
931 Der_type thistype;
932 int thistag;
933 int e;
934
935 e = der_get_tag(p, len, &thisclass, &thistype, &thistag, &l);
936 if (e)
937 return (e);
938 if (xclass != thisclass || type != thistype)
939 return (ASN1_BAD_ID);
940 if (tag > thistag)
941 return (ASN1_MISPLACED_FIELD);
942 if (tag < thistag)
943 return (ASN1_MISSING_FIELD);
944 if (size)
945 *size = l;
946 return (0);
947}
948
949static int
950der_match_tag_and_length(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
951 Der_class xclass, Der_type type, int tag,
952 size_t *length_ret, size_t *size)
953{
954 size_t l, ret = 0;
955 int e;
956
957 e = der_match_tag(p, len, xclass, type, tag, &l);
958 if (e)
959 return (e);
960 p += l;
961 len -= l;
962 ret += l;
963 e = der_get_length(p, len, length_ret, &l);
964 if (e)
965 return (e);
966 /* p += l; */
967 len -= l;
968 POST(len);
969 ret += l;
970 if (size)
971 *size = ret;
972 return (0);
973}

975static int
976decode_enumerated(const unsigned char *p, size_t len, void *num, size_t *size)
977{
978 size_t ret = 0;
979 size_t l, reallen;
980 int e;
981
982 e = der_match_tag(p, len, ASN1_C_UNIV, PRIM, UT_Enumerated, &l);
983 if (e)
984 return (e);
985 p += l;
986 len -= l;
987 ret += l;
988 e = der_get_length(p, len, &reallen, &l);
989 if (e)
990 return (e);
991 p += l;
992 len -= l;
993 ret += l;
994 e = der_get_int(p, reallen, num, &l);
995 if (e)
996 return (e);
997 p += l;
998 len -= l;
999 POST(p); POST(len);
1000 ret += l;
1001 if (size)
1002 *size = ret;
1003 return (0);
1004}

1006static int
1007decode_octet_string(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,

1009{
1010 size_t ret = 0;

1012 int e;
1013 size_t slen;
1014
1015 k->data = NULL;
1016 k->length = 0;
1017
1018 e = der_match_tag(p, len, ASN1_C_UNIV, PRIM, UT_OctetString, &l);

1020 return (e);

1023 ret += l;
1024

1027 return (e);

1041 if (size)
1042 *size = ret;
1043 return (0);
1044}

1094/* der_length.c */
1095
1096static size_t
1097len_unsigned(unsigned val)
1098{
1099 size_t ret = 0;
1100
1101 do {
1102 ++ret;
1103 val /= 256;
1104 } while (val);
1105 return (ret);
1106}
1107
1108static size_t
1109length_len(size_t len)
1110{
1111 if (len < 128U)
1112 return (1);
1113 else
1114 return (len_unsigned((unsigned int)len) + 1);
1115}

1117
1118/* der_put.c */
1119
1120/*
1121 * All encoding functions take a pointer `p' to first position in which to
1122 * write, from the right, `len' which means the maximum number of characters
1123 * we are able to write. The function returns the number of characters
1124 * written in `size' (if non-NULL). The return value is 0 or an error.
1125 */
1126
1127static int
1128der_put_unsigned(unsigned char *p, size_t len, unsigned val, size_t *size)
1129{
1130 unsigned char *base = p;
1131
1132 if (val) {
1133 while (len > 0U && val) {
1134 *p-- = val % 256;
1135 val /= 256;
1136 --len;
1137 }
1138 if (val != 0)
1139 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1140 else {
1141 *size = base - p;
1142 return (0);
1143 }
1144 } else if (len < 1U)
1145 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1146 else {
1147 *p = 0;
1148 *size = 1;
1149 return (0);
1150 }
1151}
1152
1153static int
1154der_put_int(unsigned char *p, size_t len, int val, size_t *size)
1155{
1156 unsigned char *base = p;
1157
1158 if (val >= 0) {
1159 do {
1160 if (len < 1U)
1161 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1162 *p-- = val % 256;
1163 len--;
1164 val /= 256;
1165 } while (val);
1166 if (p[1] >= 128) {
1167 if (len < 1U)
1168 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1169 *p-- = 0;
1170 len--;
1171 POST(len);
1172 }
1173 } else {
1174 val = ~val;
1175 do {
1176 if (len < 1U)
1177 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1178 *p-- = ~(val % 256);
1179 len--;
1180 val /= 256;
1181 } while (val);
1182 if (p[1] < 128) {
1183 if (len < 1U)
1184 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1185 *p-- = 0xff;
1186 len--;
1187 POST(len);
1188 }
1189 }
1190 *size = base - p;
1191 return (0);
1192}
1193
1194static int
1195der_put_length(unsigned char *p, size_t len, size_t val, size_t *size)
1196{
1197 if (len < 1U)
1198 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1199 if (val < 128U) {
1200 *p = (unsigned char)val;
1201 *size = 1;
1202 return (0);
1203 } else {
1204 size_t l;
1205 int e;
1206
1207 e = der_put_unsigned(p, len - 1, (unsigned int)val, &l);
1208 if (e)
1209 return (e);
1210 p -= l;
1211 *p = 0x80 | (unsigned char)l;
1212 *size = l + 1;
1213 return (0);
1214 }
1215}
1216
1217static int
1218der_put_octet_string(unsigned char *p, size_t len,
1219 const octet_string *data, size_t *size)
1220{
1221 if (len < data->length)
1222 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1223 p -= data->length;
1224 len -= data->length;
1225 POST(len);
1226 memmove(p + 1, data->data, data->length);
1227 *size = data->length;
1228 return (0);
1229}
1230
1231static int
1232der_put_oid(unsigned char *p, size_t len,
1233 const oid *data, size_t *size)
1234{
1235 unsigned char *base = p;
1236 size_t n;
1237
1238 for (n = data->length; n >= 3u; --n) {
1239 unsigned u = data->components[n - 1];
1240
1241 if (len < 1U)
1242 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1243 *p-- = u % 128;
1244 u /= 128;
1245 --len;
1246 while (u > 0) {
1247 if (len < 1U)
1248 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1249 *p-- = 128 + u % 128;
1250 u /= 128;
1251 --len;
1252 }
1253 }
1254 if (len < 1U)
1255 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1256 *p-- = 40 * data->components[0] + data->components[1];
1257 *size = base - p;
1258 return (0);
1259}
1260
1261static int
1262der_put_tag(unsigned char *p, size_t len, Der_class xclass, Der_type type,
1263 int tag, size_t *size)
1264{
1265 if (len < 1U)
1266 return (ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1267 *p = (xclass << 6) | (type << 5) | tag; /* XXX */
1268 *size = 1;
1269 return (0);
1270}

1273der_put_length_and_tag(unsigned char *p, size_t len, size_t len_val,
1274 Der_class xclass, Der_type type, int tag, size_t *size)
1275{
1276 size_t ret = 0;
1277 size_t l;
1278 int e;
1279
1280 e = der_put_length(p, len, len_val, &l);
1281 if (e)
1282 return (e);
1283 p -= l;
1284 len -= l;
1285 ret += l;
1286 e = der_put_tag(p, len, xclass, type, tag, &l);
1287 if (e)
1288 return (e);
1289 p -= l;
1290 len -= l;
1291 POST(p); POST(len);
1292 ret += l;
1293 *size = ret;
1294 return (0);
1295}

1373/* encapsulate.c */
1374
1375static void
1376gssapi_encap_length(size_t data_len,
1377 size_t *len,
1378 size_t *total_len,
1379 const gss_OID mech)
1380{
1381 size_t len_len;
1382
1383 *len = 1 + 1 + mech->length + data_len;
1384
1385 len_len = length_len(*len);
1386
1387 *total_len = 1 + len_len + *len;
1388}
1389
1390static u_char *
1391gssapi_mech_make_header(u_char *p,
1392 size_t len,
1393 const gss_OID mech)
1394{
1395 int e;
1396 size_t len_len, foo;
1397
1398 *p++ = 0x60;
1399 len_len = length_len(len);
1400 e = der_put_length(p + len_len - 1, len_len, len, &foo);
1401 if (e || foo != len_len)
1402 return (NULL);
1403 p += len_len;
1404 *p++ = 0x06;
1405 *p++ = mech->length;
1406 memmove(p, mech->elements, mech->length);
1407 p += mech->length;
1408 return (p);
1409}
1410
1411/*
1412 * Give it a krb5_data and it will encapsulate with extra GSS-API wrappings.
1413 */
1414
1415static OM_uint32
1416gssapi_spnego_encapsulate(OM_uint32 * minor_status,
1417 unsigned char *buf,
1418 size_t buf_size,
1419 gss_buffer_t output_token,
1420 const gss_OID mech)
1421{
1422 size_t len, outer_len;
1423 u_char *p;
1424
1425 gssapi_encap_length(buf_size, &len, &outer_len, mech);
1426
1427 output_token->length = outer_len;
1428 output_token->value = malloc(outer_len);
1429 if (output_token->value == NULL) {
1430 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
1431 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
1432 }
1433 p = gssapi_mech_make_header(output_token->value, len, mech);
1434 if (p == NULL) {
1435 if (output_token->length != 0U)
1436 gss_release_buffer(minor_status, output_token);
1437 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
1438 }
1439 memmove(p, buf, buf_size);
1440 return (GSS_S_COMPLETE);
1441}

1443/* init_sec_context.c */
1444/*
1445 * SPNEGO wrapper for Kerberos5 GSS-API kouril@ics.muni.cz, 2003 (mostly
1446 * based on Heimdal code)
1447 */
1448
1449static int
1450add_mech(MechTypeList * mech_list, gss_OID mech)
1451{
1452 MechType *tmp;
1453 int ret;
1454
1455 tmp = realloc(mech_list->val, (mech_list->len + 1) * sizeof(*tmp));
1456 if (tmp == NULL)
1457 return (ENOMEM);
1458 mech_list->val = tmp;
1459
1460 ret = der_get_oid(mech->elements, mech->length,
1461 &mech_list->val[mech_list->len], NULL);
1462 if (ret)
1463 return (ret);
1464
1465 mech_list->len++;
1466 return (0);
1467}
1468
1469/*
1470 * return the length of the mechanism in token or -1
1471 * (which implies that the token was bad - GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN
1472 */
1473
1474static ssize_t
1475gssapi_krb5_get_mech(const u_char *ptr,
1476 size_t total_len,
1477 const u_char **mech_ret)
1478{
1479 size_t len, len_len, mech_len, foo;
1480 const u_char *p = ptr;
1481 int e;
1482
1483 if (total_len < 1U)
1484 return (-1);
1485 if (*p++ != 0x60)
1486 return (-1);
1487 e = der_get_length (p, total_len - 1, &len, &len_len);
1488 if (e || 1 + len_len + len != total_len)
1489 return (-1);
1490 p += len_len;
1491 if (*p++ != 0x06)
1492 return (-1);
1493 e = der_get_length (p, total_len - 1 - len_len - 1,
1494 &mech_len, &foo);
1495 if (e)
1496 return (-1);
1497 p += foo;
1498 *mech_ret = p;
1499 return (mech_len);
1500}
1501
1502static OM_uint32
1503spnego_initial(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
1504 const gss_cred_id_t initiator_cred_handle,
1505 gss_ctx_id_t *context_handle,
1506 const gss_name_t target_name,
1507 const gss_OID mech_type,
1508 OM_uint32 req_flags,
1509 OM_uint32 time_req,
1510 const gss_channel_bindings_t input_chan_bindings,
1511 const gss_buffer_t input_token,
1512 gss_OID *actual_mech_type,
1513 gss_buffer_t output_token,
1514 OM_uint32 *ret_flags,
1515 OM_uint32 *time_rec)
1516{
1517 NegTokenInit token_init;
1518 OM_uint32 major_status, minor_status2;
1519 gss_buffer_desc krb5_output_token = GSS_C_EMPTY_BUFFER;
1520 unsigned char *buf = NULL;
1521 size_t buf_size;
1522 size_t len = 0; /* XXX: gcc */
1523 int ret;
1524
1525 (void)mech_type;
1526
1527 memset(&token_init, 0, sizeof(token_init));
1528
1529 ret = add_mech(&token_init.mechTypes, GSS_KRB5_MECH);
1530 if (ret) {
1531 *minor_status = ret;
1532 ret = GSS_S_FAILURE;
1533 goto end;
1534 }
1535
1536 major_status = gss_init_sec_context(minor_status,
1537 initiator_cred_handle,
1538 context_handle,
1539 target_name,
1540 GSS_KRB5_MECH,
1541 req_flags,
1542 time_req,
1543 input_chan_bindings,
1544 input_token,
1545 actual_mech_type,
1546 &krb5_output_token,
1547 ret_flags,
1548 time_rec);
1549 if (GSS_ERROR(major_status)) {
1550 ret = major_status;
1551 goto end;
1552 }
1553 if (krb5_output_token.length > 0U) {
1554 token_init.mechToken = malloc(sizeof(*token_init.mechToken));
1555 if (token_init.mechToken == NULL) {
1556 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
1557 ret = GSS_S_FAILURE;
1558 goto end;
1559 }
1560 token_init.mechToken->data = krb5_output_token.value;
1561 token_init.mechToken->length = krb5_output_token.length;
1562 }
1563 /*
1564 * The MS implementation of SPNEGO seems to not like the mechListMIC
1565 * field, so we omit it (it's optional anyway)
1566 */
1567
1568 buf_size = 1024;
1569 buf = malloc(buf_size);
1570 if (buf == NULL) {
1571 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
1572 ret = GSS_S_FAILURE;
1573 goto end;
1574 }
1575
1576 do {
1577 ret = encode_NegTokenInit(buf + buf_size - 1,
1578 buf_size,
1579 &token_init, &len);
1580 if (ret == 0) {
1581 size_t tmp;
1582
1583 ret = der_put_length_and_tag(buf + buf_size - len - 1,
1584 buf_size - len,
1585 len,
1586 ASN1_C_CONTEXT,
1587 CONS,
1588 0,
1589 &tmp);
1590 if (ret == 0)
1591 len += tmp;
1592 }
1593 if (ret) {
1594 if (ret == ASN1_OVERFLOW) {
1595 u_char *tmp;
1596
1597 buf_size *= 2;
1598 tmp = realloc(buf, buf_size);
1599 if (tmp == NULL) {
1600 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
1601 ret = GSS_S_FAILURE;
1602 goto end;
1603 }
1604 buf = tmp;
1605 } else {
1606 *minor_status = ret;
1607 ret = GSS_S_FAILURE;
1608 goto end;
1609 }
1610 }
1611 } while (ret == ASN1_OVERFLOW);
1612
1613 ret = gssapi_spnego_encapsulate(minor_status,
1614 buf + buf_size - len, len,
1615 output_token, GSS_SPNEGO_MECH);
1616 if (ret == GSS_S_COMPLETE)
1617 ret = major_status;
1618
1619end:
1620 if (token_init.mechToken != NULL) {
1621 free(token_init.mechToken);
1622 token_init.mechToken = NULL;
1623 }
1624 free_NegTokenInit(&token_init);
1625 if (krb5_output_token.length != 0U)
1626 gss_release_buffer(&minor_status2, &krb5_output_token);
1627 if (buf)
1628 free(buf);
1629
1630 return (ret);
1631}
1632
1633static OM_uint32
1634spnego_reply(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
1635 const gss_cred_id_t initiator_cred_handle,
1636 gss_ctx_id_t *context_handle,
1637 const gss_name_t target_name,
1638 const gss_OID mech_type,
1639 OM_uint32 req_flags,
1640 OM_uint32 time_req,
1641 const gss_channel_bindings_t input_chan_bindings,
1642 const gss_buffer_t input_token,
1643 gss_OID *actual_mech_type,
1644 gss_buffer_t output_token,
1645 OM_uint32 *ret_flags,
1646 OM_uint32 *time_rec)
1647{
1648 OM_uint32 ret;
1649 NegTokenResp resp;
1650 unsigned char *buf;
1651 size_t buf_size;
1652 u_char oidbuf[17];
1653 size_t oidlen;
1654 gss_buffer_desc sub_token;
1655 ssize_t mech_len;
1656 const u_char *p;
1657 size_t len, taglen;
1658
1659 (void)mech_type;
1660
1661 output_token->length = 0;
1662 output_token->value = NULL;
1663
1664 /*
1665 * SPNEGO doesn't include gss wrapping on SubsequentContextToken
1666 * like the Kerberos 5 mech does. But lets check for it anyway.
1667 */
1668
1669 mech_len = gssapi_krb5_get_mech(input_token->value,
1670 input_token->length,
1671 &p);
1672
1673 if (mech_len < 0) {
1674 buf = input_token->value;
1675 buf_size = input_token->length;
1676 } else if ((size_t)mech_len == GSS_KRB5_MECH->length &&
1677 isc_safe_memequal(GSS_KRB5_MECH->elements, p, mech_len))
1678 return (gss_init_sec_context(minor_status,
1679 initiator_cred_handle,
1680 context_handle,
1681 target_name,
1682 GSS_KRB5_MECH,
1683 req_flags,
1684 time_req,
1685 input_chan_bindings,
1686 input_token,
1687 actual_mech_type,
1688 output_token,
1689 ret_flags,
1690 time_rec));
1691 else if ((size_t)mech_len == GSS_SPNEGO_MECH->length &&
1692 isc_safe_memequal(GSS_SPNEGO_MECH->elements, p, mech_len)) {
1693 ret = gssapi_spnego_decapsulate(minor_status,
1694 input_token,
1695 &buf,
1696 &buf_size,
1697 GSS_SPNEGO_MECH);
1698 if (ret)
1699 return (ret);
1700 } else
1701 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
1702
1703 ret = der_match_tag_and_length(buf, buf_size,
1704 ASN1_C_CONTEXT, CONS, 1, &len, &taglen);
1705 if (ret)
1706 return (ret);
1707
1708 if(len > buf_size - taglen)
1709 return (ASN1_OVERRUN);
1710
1711 ret = decode_NegTokenResp(buf + taglen, len, &resp, NULL);
1712 if (ret) {
1713 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
1714 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
1715 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
1716 }
1717
1718 if (resp.negState == NULL ||
1719 *(resp.negState) == reject ||
1720 resp.supportedMech == NULL) {
1721 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
1722 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
1723 }
1724
1725 ret = der_put_oid(oidbuf + sizeof(oidbuf) - 1,
1726 sizeof(oidbuf),
1727 resp.supportedMech,
1728 &oidlen);
1729 if (ret || oidlen != GSS_KRB5_MECH->length ||
1730 !isc_safe_memequal(oidbuf + sizeof(oidbuf) - oidlen,
1731 GSS_KRB5_MECH->elements, oidlen))
1732 {
1733 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
1734 return GSS_S_BAD_MECH;
1735 }
1736
1737 if (resp.responseToken != NULL) {
1738 sub_token.length = resp.responseToken->length;
1739 sub_token.value = resp.responseToken->data;
1740 } else {
1741 sub_token.length = 0;
1742 sub_token.value = NULL;
1743 }
1744
1745 ret = gss_init_sec_context(minor_status,
1746 initiator_cred_handle,
1747 context_handle,
1748 target_name,
1749 GSS_KRB5_MECH,
1750 req_flags,
1751 time_req,
1752 input_chan_bindings,
1753 &sub_token,
1754 actual_mech_type,
1755 output_token,
1756 ret_flags,
1757 time_rec);
1758 if (ret) {
1759 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
1760 return (ret);
1761 }
1762
1763 /*
1764 * XXXSRA I don't think this limited implementation ever needs
1765 * to check the MIC -- our preferred mechanism (Kerberos)
1766 * authenticates its own messages and is the only mechanism
1767 * we'll accept, so if the mechanism negotiation completes
1768 * successfully, we don't need the MIC. See RFC 4178.
1769 */
1770
1771 free_NegTokenResp(&resp);
1772 return (ret);
1773}

1776
1777OM_uint32
1778gss_init_sec_context_spnego(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
1779 const gss_cred_id_t initiator_cred_handle,
1780 gss_ctx_id_t *context_handle,
1781 const gss_name_t target_name,
1782 const gss_OID mech_type,
1783 OM_uint32 req_flags,
1784 OM_uint32 time_req,
1785 const gss_channel_bindings_t input_chan_bindings,
1786 const gss_buffer_t input_token,
1787 gss_OID *actual_mech_type,
1788 gss_buffer_t output_token,
1789 OM_uint32 *ret_flags,
1790 OM_uint32 *time_rec)
1791{
1792 /* Dirty trick to suppress compiler warnings */
1793
1794 /* Figure out whether we're starting over or processing a reply */
1795
1796 if (input_token == GSS_C_NO_BUFFER || input_token->length == 0U)
1797 return (spnego_initial(minor_status,
1798 initiator_cred_handle,
1799 context_handle,
1800 target_name,
1801 mech_type,
1802 req_flags,
1803 time_req,
1804 input_chan_bindings,
1805 input_token,
1806 actual_mech_type,
1807 output_token,
1808 ret_flags,
1809 time_rec));
1810 else
1811 return (spnego_reply(minor_status,
1812 initiator_cred_handle,
1813 context_handle,
1814 target_name,
1815 mech_type,
1816 req_flags,
1817 time_req,
1818 input_chan_bindings,
1819 input_token,
1820 actual_mech_type,
1821 output_token,
1822 ret_flags,
1823 time_rec));
1824}
